<statement>
<p>If a right triangle has legs of length <m>\displaystyle{a}={14}</m> and <m>\displaystyle{b}={29}</m>, what are the angles</p>
<p>
  opposite from side of length <m>\displaystyle{a}</m>: <m>\displaystyle{A}=</m> <input type="text" style="width:4.6ch" name="qn1000" id="qn1000" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 1 of 2" class="text"/><circumflex/><m>\displaystyle\circ</m> </p>
<p>
  opposite from side of length <m>\displaystyle{b}</m>: <m>\displaystyle{B}=</m> <input type="text" style="width:4.6ch" name="qn1001" id="qn1001" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1 Part 2 of 2" class="text"/><circumflex/><m>\displaystyle\circ</m> </p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>26</li><li>64</li></ul></p><p>For angle <m>\displaystyle{A}</m> the opposite side has length <m>\displaystyle{a}={14}</m> and the adjacent side has length <m>\displaystyle{b}={29}</m>. The angle is therefore</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{A}={\arctan{{\left(\frac{{14}}{{29}}\right)}}}\approx{25.769327624339}^{\circ}\approx{26}^{\circ}</m>.</p>
<p>For angle <m>\displaystyle{B}</m> the opposite side has length <m>\displaystyle{b}={29}</m> and the adjacent side has length <m>\displaystyle{a}={14}</m>. The angle is therefore</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{B}={\arctan{{\left(\frac{{29}}{{14}}\right)}}}\approx{64.230672375661}^{\circ}\approx{64}^{\circ}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>